commentary: Harbhajan Singh to Miller, OUT Harbhajan strikes, Rahane pouches it at backward point. Harbhajan tosses this up generously outside off, some turn as well, Miller has a crack at it but his bat twists and he slices it off the outside half of the bat as Rahane moves to his right, tumbles forward to snaffle it. The strong opening stand has been broken. Who will come in at No.3?

commentary: Mishra to Amla, OUT Dhoni takes the bails off in a flash. Amla can't drag his back foot back in time. The spinners have slowed the visitors down. Flatter at 94.6ks and spins away, Amla loses his balance as he aims to drive it through the off side. He does not connect, neither can he pull his back foot in time. The TV umpire is called in and Amla departs

commentary: MM Sharma to du Plessis, 1 no ball Faf holes out to long-on. Kohli pulls off the finger-on-the-lip celebration.. Back-of-the-hand slower ball from Mohit, Faf steps out and aims a lofted strike. He is hoodwinked by the lack of pace on it. He can't manufacture his own pace either and miscues it to Kohli. Hang on, looks like Mohit has overstepped. His foot is on the line. No part of the heel behind the crease.

commentary: Harbhajan Singh to de Villiers, OUT Dhawan, who had dropped a tough chance to let Faf off, makes amends by running QdK out. This was pushed through on an off-stump line, AB works it towards short midwicket, where Dhawan flings to his left and stops the ball. QdK was late to respond, as Dhawan throws ball over to Dhoni. QdK is caught short

commentary: Patel to de Villiers, OUT Axar gets AB with an arm ball. Two wickets in two balls for India. Big, big wicket this. Arrows in, as AB goes back for a cut, he gets some bat on the attempted cut, chopping it towards point. The umpire Dar thinks it was pad first and raises his finger. Replays show that it was pad first indeed and hit in front of middle.
